But at the end of the day when playing street ball, every kid playing at one point or another had their Kobe Moment! Whats a Kobe Moment you might ask? Because no matter what team you root for, you respect a player like him!

snippet.textDisplay: You can’t help but to love Kobe. He was a Legend in the NBA and was becoming the type of person that touched millions of lives. I could see Kobe becoming a leader of not just in sports and businesses but also having the tools to become a leader of states and government. You could hear it in his conversations, see it in his interviews. He was growing and you could see it with his family life. The guy was so happy and you always saw him smiling. You hear people talk about their memories about Kobe and see the pain in their faces and you can tell Kobe was loved. Truly Loved by so many. This is going to hurt for a long time. My heart goes out to the people that were on that helicopter and I hope to God they change some of the flight standards for flying in bad weather.
